<h2>%%ReferenceStyle%%Legal authorities (cases)</h2>
<hr>
<br>
<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
A legal case is only included in your references if it is important to the understanding of your 
essay. Cases should be listed separately under the heading &#8216;Legal authorities&#8217;.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">	
	<em>Name of case</em>/ (Year)/ Volume number/ Abbreviated name of law report series/ 
	Page on which report begins
</blockquote>
<br>
When there is no volume number, place the year in square brackets.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">	
	<em>Name of case</em> [Year] Abbreviated name of law report series/ 
	Page on which report begins
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Examples</strong>
<br>
Case with volume number:
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">
	<em><span class="hover" title="Name of case">Wik Peoples v. Queensland</span></em>
	(<span class="hover" title="Year">1996</span>)
	<span class="hover" title="Volume number">187</span>
	<span class="hover" title="Abbreviated name of law report series">CLR</span>
	<span class="hover" title="Page on which report begins">1</span>
</blockquote>
<br>
Case without volume number:
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">
	<em><span class="hover" title="Name of case">Jones v. Sherlock </span></em>
	[<span class="hover" title="Year">2009</span>]
	<span class="hover" title="Abbreviated name of law report series">NSWSC</span>
	<span class="hover" title="Page on which report begins">246</span>
</blockquote>
<br>
