<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	The case, <em>Wik Peoples v. Queensland</em> (1996) 187 CLR 1&hellip;
	<br>
	<br>
	<em>Jones v. Sherlock</em> [2009] NSWSC 246, showed that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
On first mention in text, use the full citation. An abbreviated form or commonly known name can be given
in parentheses after the full citation. After that, use the abbreviated form only. e.g.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&hellip; <em>Wik Peoples v. Queensland</em> (1996) 187 CLR 1 (<em>the Wik case</em>)&hellip;
	<br>
	<br>
	<em>Jones v. Sherlock</em> [2009] NSWSC 246 (<em>Jones v. Sherlock</em>)
</blockquote>
<br>
